# ConnectWatch project conventions

## Build and run

- Build: `.\build.ps1` or `.\update-and-run.ps1 -Background`
- Dev loop with tests: `.\update-and-run.ps1 -Background -Test`
- Dashboard: `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` (port from `config.yaml` `web_port`)
- After changes to `internal/server/web/*`: rebuild `ConnectWatch.exe` and hard-refresh the browser (Ctrl+F5). Assets are embedded in the binary.

## Test

- Unit tests: `.\scripts\test.ps1` or `go test ./...`
- Dashboard e2e: app running, then `cd tests\e2e && npm test`
- When fixing a bug, add a regression test (`*_test.go` or Playwright spec).

## Code structure

- `app.js` and `widgets.js` stay monolithic — do not split into modules.
- `window.WidgetDashboard` API is stable.
- Dashboard grid rules: see `dashboard-grid-layout.mdc`.

## Release

- Never commit `ConnectWatch.exe` (gitignored build artifact).
- Ship via GitHub Releases + `update-manifest.json`.
- Use `.\scripts\release.ps1 -Version vX.Y.Z -Notes "..."` after human approval of the version bump.

## Cursor modes

- **Plan mode** — multi-file features, layout migrations, API/schema changes.
- **Debug mode** — intermittent bugs; use logs in `data/ConnectWatch-app.log` and `data/ConnectWatch_Log.txt`.
- **IDE browser** — dashboard UI work at `http://127.0.0.1:8080/`.

## Review prompts

Before accepting large agent diffs, ask: "Is this the root cause?" and "Are there edge cases we missed?"

